</ul><h2 id="3december2001">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1463G # Date 3 December 2001</h2>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 3 December 2001 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.C.210</td>
<td>Commonwealth Training Award rate (YA)</td>
<td>Updated the maximum National Training Award.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.D.160</td>
<td>Disability (DSP, SA, CP, CA)</td>
<td>Expanded definition to CP and CA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.M.90</td>
<td>Medical condition (DSP, SA, CP, CA)</td>
<td>Expanded definition to CP and CA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.P.374</td>
<td>Prescribed pre-pension age pension</td>
<td>Replaced link to the act with a definition for historical purposes.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.3.1.10</td>
<td>Qualification for PA</td>
<td>Updated criterion.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.10.110</td>
<td>Full-time Students Satisfactory Progress - Study at the Same Level</td>
<td>Clarified policy.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.5.1.80</td>
<td>Residence Qualification for PP - Customer Absences from Australia</td>
<td>Deleted topic - see 7.1.5.60 Portability Table.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.6.20</td>
<td>Payability of MOB</td>
<td>Added information about the end date of the sales tax exemption on cars.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.1.20</td>
<td>Qualification for Low Income HCC</td>
<td>Added eligibility of prisoners and detainees to claim low income HCC.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.1.50</td>
<td>General provisions for Dependents &amp; HCCs</td>
<td>Updated policy for tertiary students.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.1.70</td>
<td>Low Income HCC - Assessment of Income</td>
<td>Changed reference to income to ordinary income.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.2.10</td>
<td>Qualification for PCC</td>
<td>Amended to reflect qualification for PCC for customer over 60.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.9.3.10</td>
<td>Qualification for CSHC</td>
<td>Added reference to low income HCC holders and the CSHC.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.1.20</td>
<td>General Provisions for Assessing Income</td>
<td>Added policy on income streams funded from successor funds.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.3.10</td>
<td>Income Assessment of Asset-test Exempt Income Streams</td>
<td>Clarified existing provisions.</td>
</tr><tr><td>6.2.6.10</td>
<td>SpB Reviews - Mail and Intensive Reviews</td>
<td>Updated references to field reviews.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2 id="5november2001">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1462G # Date 5 November 2001</h2>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 5 November 2001 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.B.70</td>
<td>Board &amp; lodging (RA, SpB)</td>
<td>Updated policy and added examples.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.F.05</td>
<td>Faecal Incontinence</td>
<td>Added new key term.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.P.430</td>
<td>Profoundly disabled child (CP)</td>
<td>Updated policy references.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.Q.35</td>
<td>Qualifying Residence Exemption</td>
<td>Included reference to payability of SpB.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.T.190</td>
<td>Two or more disabled children (CP)</td>
<td>Clarified policy on requirement for all children to have severe disability or severe medical condition.</td>
</tr><tr><td>2.2.1</td>
<td>Verifying POI</td>
<td>Updated section due to changes to procedures.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.2.70</td>
<td>Exemptions from Waiting Periods</td>
<td>Removed the word 'another' from last line of first block of dot points.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.1.2.70</td>
<td>Exemptions from Waiting Periods</td>
<td>Added exemption from the OWP.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.3.10</td>
<td>Qualification for YA</td>
<td>Added CDEP exception for activity test purposes.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.2.8.90</td>
<td>Approved Activity - Other Activities that May satisfy the Activity Test</td>
<td>Updated policy on performers.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.5.1.50</td>
<td>Child-related Qualification for PP - Shared Care</td>
<td>Updated policy.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.1.10</td>
<td>Qualification for DSP</td>
<td>Included information about refugees being able to satisfy residential qualifications for DSP.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.1.100</td>
<td>Continuation, Variation or Termination of DSP</td>
<td>Clarified 2 year suspension rule and retention of PCC for 12 months when returning to work.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.2.200</td>
<td>DSP Customers with Less than 10 Years Residence</td>
<td>Included information about refugees being able to satisfy residential qualifications for DSP.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.3.130</td>
<td>Assessing DSP when a Customer has been an Australian Resident for Less than 10 Years and has Never Worked</td>
<td>Updated references to CDA to CA.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.4.10</td>
<td>Qualification for CP</td>
<td>Added a link to the definition of 'permanently or for an extended period (CP, CA)'.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.4.50</td>
<td>Qualification for CP during Temporary Absence from the Private Home - Hospitalisation</td>
<td>Revised policy.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.5.10</td>
<td>Qualification for SA</td>
<td>Updated definition of work for Sickness Allowance.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.6.50</td>
<td>Assessment of other criteria for MOB</td>
<td>Added details re private study hours counting toward the 8 hour requirement for vocational training.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.6.7.30</td>
<td>Qualification for CA</td>
<td>Updated criterion table.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.1.20</td>
<td>Payability of SpB</td>
<td>Removed duplicate entry from table.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.2.70</td>
<td>SpB for Customers Under 18 Years of Age</td>
<td>Clarified date of the case discussion.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.4.20</td>
<td>Qualification for CP - Extreme Circumstances (domestic &amp; family violence)</td>
<td>Added provisions for persons with court orders.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.4.70</td>
<td>Payability of CrP - Released prisoners</td>
<td>Removed note regarding release from gaol or psychiatric confinement.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.5</td>
<td>Activity Testing of SpB Recipients</td>
<td>Added new section.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.5.10</td>
<td>What is the SpB Activity Test?</td>
<td>Added new topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.5.20</td>
<td>Who does the SpB Activity Test Apply to?</td>
<td>Added new topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.5.30</td>
<td>SpB Activity Test Exemptions</td>
<td>Added new topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.7.5.40</td>
<td>Non-compliance with SpB Activity Test</td>
<td>Added new topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>3.8.10.70</td>
<td>Bereavement Payments for CPS</td>
<td>Corrected mathematical symbols.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.2.11</td>
<td>Carer Payment (CP) Income and Assets Tests</td>
<td>Updated information on the income and assets for non-customer care receivers.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.2.31</td>
<td>Other Income Exempt from Assessment - Specifically Approved</td>
<td>Added to list of exempt lump sums.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.4.10</td>
<td>Application of the Income Maintenance Period</td>
<td>Removed procedural note.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.6.50</td>
<td>Arrears, Embargoes &amp; Exchange Rates for Overseas Income</td>
<td>Removed reference to assessment for FA purposes.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.8.30</td>
<td>Income from Real Estate</td>
<td>Added act reference.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.3.9.40</td>
<td>Income from Education &amp; Training Allowances</td>
<td>Clarified the treatment of scholarships awarded within Australia.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.5.110</td>
<td>Assessing Failed Financial Investments - Loans</td>
<td>Clarified policy.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.6.6.20</td>
<td>Overseas Real Estate, Partner's Share of a Business &amp; Assets Not Readily accessible</td>
<td>Corrected details concerning partner's share of business assets.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.7.2.30</td>
<td>Treatment of Assessable Assets from Private Companies</td>
<td>Amended incorrect reference to irrecoverable loans.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.1.20</td>
<td>General Provisions for Assessing Income Streams</td>
<td>Updated information on commutation of lifetime income stream prior to age pension age to life expectancy income stream after age pension age.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.9.2.40</td>
<td>Actuarial Valuation Certificate - Self-Managed Superannuation Funds and Small APRA Superannuation Funds</td>
<td>Removed references to pre1/7/2001 treatment of superannuation funds.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.1.50</td>
<td>Exemptions from the compensation provisions</td>
<td>Amended policy regarding when a social security payment is exempt from the compensation provision.</td>
</tr><tr><td>4.13.2.30</td>
<td>Compensation Part of Lump Sum - 50% rule</td>
<td>Amended table regarding application of the 50% rule.</td>
</tr><tr><td>7.1.1.10</td>
<td>Overview of Portability Legislation</td>
<td>Added act references.</td>
</tr><tr><td>7.1.5.60</td>
<td>Portability Table</td>
<td>Clarified policy on portability for humanitarian purpose.</td>
</tr></tbody></table><h2 id="2october2001">Guide to Social Security Law Update 1461G # Date 2 October 2001</h2>
<table summary="This table lists the pages changed for the 2 October 2001 release with details of the change"><thead><tr><th scope="col">Topic No</th>
<th scope="col">Topic Title</th>
<th scope="col">Details</th>
</tr></thead><tbody><tr><td>1.1.A.356</td>
<td>Average weekly earnings</td>
<td>Updated act reference following passage of Family &amp; Community Services Legislation (Simplification &amp; Other Measures) Act 2001.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.C.88</td>
<td>CA adult (CA)</td>
<td>Updated definition with a link to 1.1.D.171.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.C.115</td>
<td>Child (HCC)</td>
<td>Deleted topic.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.C.240</td>
<td>Compensation</td>
<td>Updated definition.</td>
</tr><tr><td>1.1.D.65</td>
<td>Dependant (HCC)</td>
<td>Updated policy.</td>
